SIMPLE: encampment
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Encampment
<hw>En*camp"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
act of pitching tents or forming huts, as by an army or traveling
company, for temporary lodging or rest.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The place where an army or a company is encamped; a
camp; tents pitched or huts erected for temporary lodgings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A square of about seven hundred yards was sufficient for the
<qex>encampment</qex> of twenty thousand Romans.</q>
<rj><qau>Gibbon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A green <qex>encampment</qex> yonder meets the eye.</q>
<rj><qau>Guardian.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Encanker</ent>⟦br⟧
